{"type":"message","id":"07e2e54b","parentId":"771b2ada","timestamp":"2026-03-24T06:43:49.084Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_6tzy9jz1phdi_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 5134\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=3071\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] src/tic-classifier.ps1\r\n[mutation proposed] src/tic-classifier.ps1\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 024314 - The COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight is documented but not yet tested. I need to implement the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier to validate the hypothesis that causal discovery = invariant finding.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"crisp-sable","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 5134\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=3071\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] src/tic-classifier.ps1\r\n[mutation proposed] src/tic-classifier.ps1\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 024314 - The COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight is documented but not yet tested. I need to implement the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier to validate the hypothesis that causal discovery = invariant finding.\r\n","name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774334629082}}
{"type":"message","id":"46cb18e9","parentId":"07e2e54b","timestamp":"2026-03-24T06:43:49.086Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_6tzy9jz1phdi_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 024114\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the next concrete action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n2. Key pending item: \"Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\"\r\n3. The session has identified COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY as the key insight\r\n4. Next action should be the TIC Experiment\r\n\r\nI need to:\r\n1. Read the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md to understand the TIC approach\r\n2. Look at the pulse logs to understand their format\r\n3. Create a TIC classifier implementation\r\n\r\nLet me first check what files exist and understand the structure better. I'll look at:\r\n- research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md for the experiment design\r\n- A recent pulse log to understand the format\r\n- Then implement the TIC classifier\r\n\r\nThis is a concrete file edit action that advances the Phase 1 advancement goal.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next priority action to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. I need to examine the pulse log format and the duality document, then implement the classifier.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nReview the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md specification and a sample pulse log, then implement the TIC classifier as a Python script that:\r\n1. Parses recent pulse logs\r\n2. Extracts features that indicate invariant vs variant content\r\n3. Classifies pulse elements and predicts next pulse content\r\n4. Reports accuracy metrics against success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction)\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\n# Tests hypothesis: causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n# Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nPULSE_LOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nMIN_RECENT = 10  # minimum pulse logs to analyze\r\n\r\ndef extract_pulse_elements(pulse_path):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract structured elements from a pulse log.\"\"\"\r\n    with open(pulse_path, 'r') as f:\r\n        content = f.read()\r\n    \r\n    elements = {\r\n        'goals_mentioned': [],\r\n        'files_mentioned': [],\r\n        'actions_taken': [],\r\n        'key_insights': [],\r\n        'pending_items': []\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Extract goal references\r\n    goals = re.findall(r'(Phase \\d|Goal:|# \\w+ COMPLETE|# Pending)', content)\r\n    elements['goals_mentioned'] = goals\r\n    \r\n    # Extract file references\r\n    files = re.findall(r'([\\w\\-/]+\\.(md|ps1|py|txt))', content)\r\n    elements['files_mentioned'] = [f[0] for f in files]\r\n    \r\n    # Extract action patterns\r\n    actions = re.findall(r'(### ACTION\\n(.*?)(?=\\n###|\\Z))', content, re.DOTALL)\r\n    elements['actions_taken'] = [a[1].strip()[:100] for a in actions if a[1].strip()]\r\n    \r\n    # Extract insight patterns\r\n    insights = re.findall(r'\\d+\\.\\s+\\*\\*[^*]+\\*\\*[:\\s-]+(.+)', content)\r\n    elements['key_insights'] = insights\r\n    \r\n    return elements\r\n\r\ndef compute_invariance_score(element, all_elements):\r\n    \"\"\"Score how invariant an element is across pulses.\"\"\"\r\n    if not element:\r\n        return 0.0\r\n    \r\n    # Count occurrences of this element type\r\n    element_type = type(element).__name__\r\n    \r\n    # Invariant = appears consistently across many pulses\r\n    # Variant = appears in few pulses or changes frequently\r\n    \r\n    if hasattr(element, 'count'):\r\n        count = element.count\r\n        total_pulses = len(all_elements)\r\n        consistency = count / total_pulses\r\n    else:\r\n        consistency = 0.5\r\n    \r\n    return consistency\r\n\r\ndef classify_invariants(pulses):\r\n    \"\"\"Classify elements as invariant or variant.\"\"\"\r\n    all_elements = []\r\n    for pulse in pulses:\r\n        all_elements.extend(pulse.get('goals_mentioned', []))\r\n        all_elements.extend(pulse.get('files_mentioned', []))\r\n        all_elements.extend(pulse.get('actions_taken', []))\r\n    \r\n    element_counts = Counter(all_elements)\r\n    \r\n    # Threshold for invariance: appears in >50% of pulses\r\n    threshold = len(pulses) * 0.5\r\n    \r\n    invariants = {elem for elem, count in element_counts.items() if count >= threshold}\r\n    variants = {elem for elem, count in element_counts.items() if count < threshold}\r\n    \r\n    return invariants, variants, element_counts\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(invariants, current_pulse):\r\n    \"\"\"Predict next pulse content based on invariants.\"\"\"\r\n    predictions = []\r\n    \r\n    # Invariants should persist\r\n    predictions.extend(list(invariants)[:5])\r\n    \r\n    # Filter current pulse elements by invariant status\r\n    for goal in current_pulse.get('goals_mentioned', []):\r\n        if goal in invariants:\r\n            predictions.append(f\"CONTINUE: {goal}\")\r\n    \r\n    return predictions\r\n\r\ndef run_tic_experiment():\r\n    \"\"\"Main experiment runner.\"\"\"\r\n    # Get recent pulse logs\r\n    pulse_files = sorted(PULSE_LOG_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"), reverse=True)[:20]\r\n    \r\n    if len(pulse_files) < MIN_RECENT:\r\n        print(f\"ERROR: Need at least {MIN_RECENT} pulse logs, found {len(pulse_files)}\")\r\n        return\r\n    \r\n    print(f\"=== TIC Experiment: Analyzing {len(pulse_files)} pulse logs ===\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 02:41:46\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774334629084}}
